cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for salient object detection, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained convolutional neural networks for feature extraction, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The integration of bottom-up and top-down cues also involves optimization and decision-making, which can be related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with RGB-D data, which is a type of multimedia data, and multimedia processing is a subfield of computer science (cs.MM).
